#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn49.45-54"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 49 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 49 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:0.2"
msgid "5. Oghavagga "
msgstr "5. Floods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:0.3"
msgid "45–54. Oghādisutta "
msgstr "45–54. Floods, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.248, sc1
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, uddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are five higher fetters. "

msgctxt "sn49.45-54:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn49.45-54:1.3"
msgid "Rūparāgo, arūparāgo, māno, uddhaccaṃ, avijjā—"
msgstr "Desire for rebirth in the realm of luminous form, desire for rebirth in the formless realm, conceit, restlessness, and ignorance. "

msgctxt "sn49.45-54:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañcuddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. "
msgstr "These are the five higher fetters. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:1.5"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya cattāro sammappadhānā bhāvetabbā. "
msgstr "The four right efforts should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters. "

msgctxt "sn49.45-54:1.6"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn49.45-54:1.7"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise. … "

msgctxt "sn49.45-54:1.8"
msgid "uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati. "
msgstr "so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are completed by development. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:1.9"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya ime cattāro sammappadhānā bhāvetabbā”ti. "
msgstr "These four right efforts should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:1.10"
msgid "(Vitthāretabbā.) "
msgstr "(To be expanded as in SN 45.171–179, with the above as the final discourse.) "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:1.11"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:1.12"
msgid "Oghavaggo pañcamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:2.1"
msgid "Ogho yogo upādānaṃ, "
msgstr "Floods, bonds, grasping, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:2.2"
msgid "ganthā anusayena ca; "
msgstr "ties, and underlying tendencies, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:2.3"
msgid "Kāmaguṇā nīvaraṇā, "
msgstr "kinds of sensual stimulation, hindrances, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:2.4"
msgid "khandhā oruddhambhāgiyāti. "
msgstr "aggregates, and fetters high and low. "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn49.45-54:2.5"
msgid "Sammappadhānasaṃyuttaṃ pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on the Right Efforts is the fifth section."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
